<br>
However, I disagree about aggro radius. Notice how when you gained levels especially when you hit 60 that mobs that are kos to you suddenly stop attacking you unless you get VERY close (think mobs in DL). As you level, your aggro radius decreases. However, your pet is stuck at level 49.<br>
<br>
Now, the big change they did recently was to make him non-kos to everything while he is not in combat. His aggro radius stayed them same, it was just that he was automatically non-kos. Now as soon as you do a /pet attack, poof, he regains his normal kos status (not to just the mob he is attacking, but any mob in his aggro radius).<br>
