<A HREF="http://morellthule.cjb.net/">Morell Thule</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaladini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 324<br> <font color=#333333>(8/16/02 8:56:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Left Undone: Pet Aggro radius</span><hr size=1> As Rhion stated though, the radius doesn't apply to the pet in the way you suggest.<br>
<br>
Mobs have a radius in which their call for help can be heard. Included in the call for help is information about the attacker (including level). <br>
<br>
If a 60 warrior attacks the mob, it will call for help and say 'help I'm being attacked by a 60 warrior'. All the mobs in the aggro radius will hear this call, but many will not respond.<br>
<br>
If your level 49 pet attacks, those same mobs would be more than willing to join the fight.<br>
<br>
You're on the right track in complaining about the adds, but the problems you're seeing are only due to the level of your pet. <br>
<br>
The way VI could change this is to boost the level of pets. I doubt they would consider reducing the 'call for help' radii which actually belong to the NPC mobs, not your pet.<br>
<br>
Pets do have their own aggro radius, and it is a big one.  This aggro radius only applies to when the mage gets hit by a mob, the pet will come to your aid from great distances..... <p>Naladini <BR>
