Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#333333>(8/19/02 10:09:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Left Undone: Pet Aggro radius</span><hr size=1> Wezloc, this is an effect of that KOS mobs are often not also social in addition as they would assist against a player anyway because of being KOS to players. But as pets are neutral and will only get attacked by social mobs so will they fight in peace beside kos mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufatherazerun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Father Azerun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(8/26/02 6:07:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.handofmana.com/images/Father4.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Left Undone: Pet Aggro radius</span><hr size=1> Although I rarely get involved in these matters, I did send feedback on this issue to Verant a few weeks ago.<br>
<br>
The problem with pets and aggro is teh same one as having lower-level players tagging along on major raids.  The scoop:<br>
<br>
Every monster, in its aggro radius (which is often larger than it appears) has a percentage chance to notice a player coming into its radius.  This percentage increases based on two components: relative closeness, and the level of the player.  Ergo, people can sometimes &quot;level pull&quot; social creatures from a group and still not gain aggro on the other creatures.  (This is an individual mob's aggro working in conjunction with the chain aggro effect of passing hate to other creatures.)<br>
<br>
Now, a magician summoning a pet remains neutral to all other creatures until he sends in that pet to attack.  Once it engages and gets on a hate list, its lower level means that teh creatures engaging in it are more likely to broadcast a wider awarenes of its presence (just as if you had a level 49 player attacking on a raid that was comprised of mostly 55th level characters).<br>
<br>
This was tested in a number of areas.. from lower levls such as in teh back courtyard of mistmoore, to at higher levels a pet's effects on teh ledge in the Halls of Testing.  On teh ledge,m sans pet, we could single pull.  The second I summoned a pet (in teh middle fo a battle, and teh pet was fighting in relative position BEHIND ME) it nonetheless pulled teh other pit mob and from there two other MOBS by chain aggro.<br>
<br>
In tight dungeons (such as doing lower levels of Chardok) where aggro control is crucial, a pet cn sadly be considered a hindrance because of its aggro raidus issues once it attacks.  <br>
<br>
The solution would be similar to teh solution they have done for pet resists: For purposes of aggro only, have pets effectively create aggro equal to the level of their caster.<br>
<br>
It is a somewhat complicated issue to explain, but one that can once again create teh cries of &quot;no pets!&quot; during raids when pets could remain very useful tools otherwise.<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=149760">Father Azerun</a> (magelo profile)<BR>
Guildleader, <a href= "http://www.handofmana.com"> Hand of Mana</a><BR>
Nameless Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uodibillauxes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odibil Lauxes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#333333>(8/26/02 7:49:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Left Undone: Pet Aggro radius</span><hr size=1> All technical garbage aside (because I know you guys love to spew that crap), I'll have to go on my own experience and agree that pets do in fact create a larger &quot;aggro radius&quot; in one way or another. Whether it is how pets relate to a social mob, or because of the pet's level, it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> does</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> exist.<br>
<br>
The following examples make me believe without a doubt that this exists.<br>
<br>
• Our party just surfaced out of the water after killing the mini burrower in Acrylia, and as the we disposed of the couple grimlings sitting up on the shore, I summoned my pet out of the water to assist. The second my pet began attacking, two grimlings from the above platform (out of aggro range) rushed down to my pet, while a conjurer kept chain nuking me. Again, these three grimlings directly attacked <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> my pet or myself until someone taunted them off of me. I was not creating any means of aggro at the time by sitting or nuking, I only sent my pet in.<br>
<br>
